reviewText: I think boxed sets are fantastic.. Sometimes.  In the case of this this set from Mill Creek.. Not so much. Oh sure the discs include all the episodes from all six seasons, along with a few interviews and outtakes/bloopers. However my complaint is about the packaging. Could Mill Creek have gotten any cheaper? Essentially this a box, with each disc in a paper sleeve, stacked on top of each other. Can we say WTF?!? Now I have to look for another case to put the disc in that's more user friendly. I suppose the dead giveaway should have been the cost.. Live and learn.
summary: Side splitting funny... packaging, not so much

reviewText: Hate the packaging.  I got this at a sale price, so I consider it hours of entertainment for very little money... a good value.  However, I dislike series sets that jam a bunch of paper sleeves into a case.  There are many other creative solutions out there, and this packaging guarantees a dissatisfied customer... either the disks will become scratched, or the entire stack of paper sleeves will fall on the floor like a game of 52-pickup the first time someone tries to open the case.I recommend a Bellagio DVD binder for this series, and for Roseanne, which has similar packaging.

reviewText: I LOVE 3rd Rock.  No words can adequately express the comic genius of John Lithgow.  The insights into the vagaries of human nature & relationships as seen by aliens from another galaxy. reviewText: I love Saturday Night Live and even though I sometimes heard "Jane, you ignorant slut!" pursuant to the Point/Counterpoint segment with Jane Curtin and Dan Aykroyd, I found Jane, one of the original cast members, really funny.  John Lithgow has hosted and just last season, Joseph Gordon-Levitt did as well. We've loved Joseph in everything we've seen him in, particularly Premium Rush and Inception.  I haven't seen Kirsten Johnston again but French Stewart is still doing his squint-eyed misanthropic character as Chef Rudy on the TV show Mom.I formally purchased this set for my hubby's birthday...of course it was at least as much for me. My son is home for spring break now and we've been watching it every night. He remembers it from when he was little.Who will ever forget the 4 aliens' astonishment at landing in human bodies where egads! you can't turn your head around enough to lick your back??  Or Dick dying his hair black, admiring himself in the mirror and exclaiming "you're GORGEOUS!!"??? I love the blast from the past bit parts with people like Jane Lynch and it's cool to be reminded from the credits that John Lithgow's son Ian plays doofus student Leon.The special features are so fun too.  I highly recommend this set...good price for all 6 seasons too.
summary: John Lithgow, Joseph Gordon-Levitt and Jane Curtin

reviewText: Someday Mill Creek will learn to package these collections better.I actually acquired this collection from a local retailer for virtually free. It was marked $4.99 by mistake but I was charged $19.99 and the retailer honored the lower price. I had to return it for another copy after finding two discs pited to the extent they were unreadable and the retailer graciously did the exchange.Rare for dvds to come defective but once in awhile it happens. BTW I recommend that when you purchase large collections of shows, ALWAYS put each and every disc into a dvd player to see if it loads, this is how I caught the two bad discs without having to watch the entire series. Which doing so would have taken longer than the retailers 15 day return policy.

reviewText: This series about a group of aliens pretending to be earthlings is very entertaining.  John Lithgow is perfect as the egotistical "head" alien.  He has a romantic relationship with earthling , Mary Albright, a prissy PhD. played by Jane Curtain.  The other aliens are represented by Joseph Gordon-Leavitt, French Stewart, and Kristen Johnson.  The situations that they find themselves in are always complicated and hilarious.  It ran through six very funny seasons.  This was a bargain on Amazon.
